  m_Name: Pipe Organs
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Pipe Organ
  description: 'Pipe organs were large and complex musical instruments found in churches
    and wealthy estates. In manor houses, they were used for entertainment, religious
    gatherings, and formal events. Owning or maintaining an organ was a clear sign
    of wealth and cultural refinement, as they required both space and skilled musicians
    to operate. '
  illustration: {fileID: 21300000, guid: ca77a6ae79e60204dab4f831f1dc59a1, type: 3}
